{"ts":1344954110184,"silentsave":true,"restoring":false,"patch":[[{"diffs":[[1,"<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <img src=\"img/example_grid.png\" alt=\"Grid\" class=\"iconk\">\n    <h1 class=\"superhero-type\">Grids</h1>\n    <h2 class=\"sidekick-type\">are the beginning</h2>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <p><small>A visual communicator has</small></p>\n    <img src=\"img/grid_blood.png\" alt=\"Grid\" class=\"iconk separate\">\n    <h3 class=\"sidekick-type\">grids in their blood</h3>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <p>To start a design</p>\n    <h3>without a grid</h3>\n    <img src=\"img/example_blueprint.png\" alt=\"Blueprint\" class=\"iconk-doublegiant\">\n    <p>is like building</p>\n    <h3>without a blueprint</h3>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <p>Let's be honest, humans are</p>\n    <h2>imperfect <small>&</small> disorganized</h2>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <p><small>Take for example,</small></p>\n    <img src=\"img/example_calculator.png\" alt=\"Calculator\" class=\"iconk separate\">\n    <h3 class=\"sidekick-type\">the calculator</h3>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <img src=\"img/pencil_64.png\" alt=\"Pencil\" class=\"iconk separate\">\n    <p>You could do calculations yourself, but doing so</p>\n    <h4 class=\"sidekick-type\">goes against what makes humans successful:</h4>\n    <h1>Tools!</h1>\n    <p><small>(we designed them to do a task we can do, only much better)</small></p>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <p>A <span class=\"highlight\">Grid</span> is a tool that improves the</p>\n    <h3>clarity of communication</h3>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <p>So when we</p>\n    <h3>begin a website</h3>\n    <p>we begin</p>\n    <h3>with a grid</h3>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <img src=\"img/infinite.png\" alt=\"Infinite\" class=\"iconk\">\n    <h2>Digital space is infinite</h2>\n    <p>and websites have two basic rules of layout</p>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span2\">\n            <img src=\"img/arrow_left_64.png\" alt=\"Horizontal\" class=\"iconk\">\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"span2\">\n            <img src=\"img/arrow_right_64.png\" alt=\"Horizontal\" class=\"iconk\">\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <p><span class=\"highlight\">Horizontal space</span> is limited to</p>\n    <h2 class=\"sidekick-type\">the screen’s width</h2>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <div>\n        <img src=\"img/arrow_up_64.png\" alt=\"Vertical\" class=\"iconk\">\n    </div>\n    <div>\n        <img src=\"img/arrow_down_64.png\" alt=\"Vertical\" class=\"iconk\">\n    </div>\n    <p><span class=\"highlight\">Vertical space</span> is</p>\n    <h2 class=\"sidekick-type\">limitless</h2>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <img src=\"img/alertcircle_64.png\" alt=\"Alert\" class=\"iconk separate\">\n    <p>With a bit of magic</p>\n    <h2 class=\"sidekick-type\">you can change these space rules</h2>\n    <p><small>(but for now let's roll with it)</small></p>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span2\">\n            <img src=\"img/arrow_down_64.png\" alt=\"Column\" class=\"iconk\">\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"span2\">\n            <img src=\"img/arrow_down_64.png\" alt=\"Column\" class=\"iconk\">\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"span2\">\n            <img src=\"img/arrow_down_64.png\" alt=\"Column\" class=\"iconk\">\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <p>Keeping with these rules,</p>\n    <h3 class=\"sidekick-type\">our grid will be column based</h3>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <h3>Safe desktop grid width:</h3>\n    <h1 class=\"hero-type\">940px</h1>\n    <p><small>(don't worry about mobile yet)</small></p>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <p><small>This breaks neatly down into several grids:</small></p>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span4\">\n            <h1>20</h1>\n            <p>columns of</p>\n            <h2 class=\"sidekick-type\">47<small>px</small></h2>\n            <p><small>+</small></p>\n            <h3 class=\"sidekick-type\">no</h3>\n            <p>gutters</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"span4\">\n            <h1>16</h1>\n            <p>columns of</p>\n            <h2 class=\"sidekick-type\">40<small>px</small></h2>\n            <p><small>+</small></p>\n            <h3>15</h3>\n            <p>gutters of</p>\n            <h4 class=\"sidekick-type\">10<small>px</small></h4>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"span4\">\n            <h1>12</h1>\n            <p>columns of</p>\n            <h2 class=\"sidekick-type\">60<small>px</small></h2>\n            <p><small>+</small></p>\n            <h3>11</h3>\n            <p>gutters of</p>\n            <h4 class=\"sidekick-type\">20<small>px</small></h4>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span4\">\n            <h1>12</h1>\n            <p>columns of</p>\n            <h2 class=\"sidekick-type\">60<small>px</small></h2>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"span4\">\n            <h1>11</h1>\n            <p>gutters of</p>\n            <h2 class=\"sidekick-type\">20<small>px</small></h2>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <p><small>We’ll begin with the last as our basic grid, which should look like the following:</small></p>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span12\">\n            <ul class=\"thumbnails pixels\">\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n            </ul>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <p><small>To build this grid, we’ll use the</small></p>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span4\">\n            <div class=\"container-left\">\n                <pre class=\"prettyprint linenums\">\n&lt;div&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;</pre>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <h3 class=\"sidekick-type\">HTML division element</h3>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <p>To build this grid, we’ll also need:</p>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span5\">\n            <p><small>a new</small></p>\n            <h1>class</h1>\n            <h4 class=\"sidekick-type\">x 2</h4>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"span1\">\n            <h1 class=\"sidekick-type\"><small>&</small></h1>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"span5\">\n            <p><small>a new</small></p>\n            <h1>CSS rule</h1>\n            <h4 class=\"sidekick-type\">x 2</h4>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <p>Let start with the grid <span class=\"highlight\">column</span></p>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span6\">\n            <div class=\"container-left\">\n                <pre class=\"prettyprint linenums\">\n&lt;div class=\"column1\"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;</pre>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <p>Creating a class for the single <span class=\"highlight\">column</span> is simple:</p>\n    <h3 class=\"sidekick-type\">class=“column1”</h3>\n    <p><small>(remember, you can name the class anything you want)</small></p>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <p><small>Now to make the class meaningful, we'll create</small></p>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span5\">\n            <div class=\"container-left\">\n                <pre class=\"prettyprint linenums\">\n.column1 {\n    width: 60px;\n    margin-left: 20px;\n}</pre>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <p>a CSS rule with a <span class=\"highlight\">class selector</span> and <span class=\"highlight\">property definitions</span> for</p>\n    <h3 class=\"sidekick-type\">width <small>&</small> margin</h3>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span6\">\n            <div class=\"container-left\">\n                <pre class=\"prettyprint linenums\">\nbody {\n    width: 940px;\n}</pre>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <p>The <span class=\"highlight\">width</span> property defines</p>\n    <h3>how wide an element will be</h3>\n    <p><small>(can be set in px, em, or %)</small></p>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <img src=\"img/alertcircle_64.png\" alt=\"Alert\" class=\"iconk separate\">\n    <p>Normally, containers resize to their contents, but</p>\n    <h3 class=\"sidekick-type\">a set width will resize contents to fit a container</h3>\n    <p><small>(setting width is like changing a container’s contents into water)</small></p>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span7\">\n            <div class=\"container-left\">\n                <pre class=\"prettyprint linenums\">\nbody {\n    margin-top: 10px;\n    margin-bottom: 10px;\n    margin-left: 10px;\n    margin-right: 10px;\n    <small>/* shorthand: T R B L */</small>\n    margin: 10px 10px 10px 10px;\n    <small>/* shorter: TB LR */</small>\n    margin: 10px 10px;\n    <small>/* shortest: TBLR */</small>\n    margin: 10px;\n}</pre>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <p>The <span class=\"highlight\">margin</span> property defines</p>\n    <h3>spacing around an element</h3>\n    <p><small>(can be set in px, em, or %)</small></p>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <img src=\"img/alertcircle_64.png\" alt=\"Alert\" class=\"iconk separate\">\n    <p>If you set the width of an element, you can use <span class=\"highlight\">margin: 0 auto;</span> to</p>\n    <h3 class=\"sidekick-type\">horizontally center it</h3>\n    <p><small>(this is like setting text-align:center; for a text element)</small></p>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <p class=\"separate\"><small>If we were to use the column now, we’d find one big problem:</small></p>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span12\">\n            <ul class=\"thumbnails pixels\">\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n            </ul>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span12\">\n            <ul class=\"thumbnails pixels\">\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n            </ul>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span12\">\n            <ul class=\"thumbnails pixels\">\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n            </ul>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span12\">\n            <ul class=\"thumbnails pixels\">\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <h2><small>...</small></h2>\n                </li>\n            </ul>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <h3>these columns are acting like rows</h3>\n    <p>o_O</p>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span5\">\n            <div class=\"container-left\">\n                <pre class=\"prettyprint linenums\">\n.column1 {\n    width: 60px;\n    margin-left: 20px;\n    float: left;\n}</pre>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <p>We want our columns to <span class=\"highlight\">float</span>, which defines</p>\n    <h3>the horizontal flow</h3>\n    <p><small>(commonly set to left, right, or none)</small></p>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <p class=\"separate\"><small>If you look closely at our columns now, you’ll see another problem:</small></p>\n    <div class=\"container-left\" style=\"margin-left:-20px; margin-top:-64px;\">\n        <img src=\"img/arrow_down_64.png\" alt=\"Arrow\" class=\"iconk-giant dim\">\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"row\" style=\"margin-left:0;\">\n        <div class=\"span12\">\n            <ul class=\"thumbnails pixels\">\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n            </ul>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <h3>we have 12 gutters, not 11</h3>\n    <p>.__.</p>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <h3 class=\"sidekick-type\">How do we remove a single gutter</h3>\n    <p>when all of our columns have a left margin of 20?</p>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <p><small>The answer is not obvious but is very simple:</small></p>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span5\">\n            <div class=\"container-left\">\n                <pre class=\"prettyprint linenums\">\n&lt;div class=\"row\"&gt;\n   <small>&lt;!--columns--&gt;</small>\n&lt;/div&gt;</pre>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"span5\">\n            <div class=\"container-left\">\n                <pre class=\"prettyprint linenums\">\n.row {\n    margin-left: -20px;\n}</pre>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <p>We need a <span class=\"highlight\">row</span> to contain all the columns</p>\n    <h3 class=\"sidekick-type\">with a negative left margin of 20 px</h3>\n    <p><small>(the negative margin pulls the row to the left, removing 1 gutter for a perfect alignment)</small></p>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <img src=\"img/alertcircle_64.png\" alt=\"Alert\" class=\"iconk separate\">\n    <p>Children are always affected by their parent's <span class=\"highlight\">transform</span>, or</p>\n    <h2 class=\"sidekick-type\">position, rotation, and scale</h2>\n    <p><small>(even if the children have their own transform)</small></p>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <div>\n        <img src=\"img/research_64.png\" alt=\"Magic\" class=\"iconk separate\">\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span7\">\n            <div class=\"container-left\">\n                <pre class=\"prettyprint linenums pre-scrollable\">\n.clearfix {\n    *zoom: 1;\n}\n.clearfix:before, .clearfix:after {\n    display: table;\n    content: \"\";\n}\n.clearfix:after {\n    clear: both;\n}</pre>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <p>Always add a <span class=\"highlight\">clearfix</span> to a floated element's parent</p>\n    <h2 class=\"sidekick-type\">to fix their width & height</h2>\n    <p><small>(by default, a floated element has no size!)</small></p>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <p><small>For your viewing pleasure, the full code:</small></p>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span6\">\n            <div class=\"container-left\">\n                <pre class=\"prettyprint linenums pre-scrollable\">\n&lt;div class=\"row clearfix\"&gt;\n   &lt;div class=\"column1\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n   &lt;div class=\"column1\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n   &lt;div class=\"column1\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n   &lt;div class=\"column1\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n   &lt;div class=\"column1\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n   &lt;div class=\"column1\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n   &lt;div class=\"column1\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n   &lt;div class=\"column1\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n   &lt;div class=\"column1\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n   &lt;div class=\"column1\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n   &lt;div class=\"column1\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n   &lt;div class=\"column1\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;</pre>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"span5\">\n            <div class=\"container-left\">\n                <pre class=\"prettyprint linenums pre-scrollable\">\n.row {\n    margin-left: -20px;\n}\n.column1 {\n    width: 60px;\n    margin-left: 20px;\n    float: left;\n}\n.clearfix {\n    <small>/* see previous */</small>\n}</pre>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <p><small>For your viewing pleasure, the working grid:</small></p>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span12\">\n            <ul class=\"thumbnails pixels\">\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n                <li class=\"span1\">\n                    <div class=\"aspect-enforcer\"></div>\n                    <div class=\"thumbnail\"></div>\n                </li>\n            </ul>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n</div>\n\n<div class=\"step container container-center\">\n    \n    <p>So how do we go from 12 to various size columns?</p>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"span7\">\n            <div class=\"container-left\">\n                <pre class=\"prettyprint linenums\">\n&lt;div class=\"row clearfix\"&gt;\n   &lt;div class=\"column2\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n   &lt;div class=\"column4\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n   &lt;div class=\"column5\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n   &lt;div class=\"column1\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;</pre>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <p><small>(hint: classes and CSS rules!)</small></p>\n    \n</div>\n\n<!--\n\nGrids are the beginning\n\nA visual communicator has grids in their blood\n\nTo start a design without a grid is like building something without instructions\n\nLet's be honest, humans are imperfect and disorganized creatures\n\nTake for example, the calculator\n\nYou could do calculations yourself, but doing so goes against everything that has made us so successful as a species: tools we designed to do a task we can do, only much better\n\nGrids are a tool that improve the organization and clarity of our communication\n\nSo when we begin a website, we begin with a grid\n\nAnd although the digital space is infinite, websites have two basic rules of layout\n\nHorizontal space is limited to the screen’s width\n\nVertical space is limitless\n\nWith a bit of magic, you can break these rules, but for now let's roll with it\n\nThis leaves us with a layout that is heavily column based\n\nA safe starting width for the desktop is 940px\n\nThis breaks neatly down into several grids\n\n20 columns of 47 px with no gutters\n\n16 columns of 40 px with 15 gutters of 10 px\n\n12 columns of 60 px with 11 gutters of 20 px\n\nWe’ll begin with the last of these as our basic grid\n\nTo build this grid, we’ll use the HTML division element\n\nTo create a reusable single column we need to define: a class + CSS rules\n\nLet’s call our class “column1” and create a CSS rule with a class selector and the properties width and margin\n\nThe width property defines how wide an element will be, and can be set in px or %\n\nNormally, containers resize to their contents, but with a set width contents will resize to fit into a container\n\nSo setting width is like changing a container’s contents into water\n\nThe margin property tells all other elements to stay a certain distance away\n\nMargins are a bit like a restraining order on the whole world\n\nIn the case of our column, the width will be 60 px and its margin-left will be the gutter space of 20 px\n\nIf we were to use the column now, we’d find one big problem: these columns don’t sit side-by-side\n\nTo make an element sit next to another, we need the float property\n\nThe float property defines whether or not an element will flow next to other elements\n\nFor our columns, we want them to float left\n\nIf you look closely at a row with 12 columns now, you’ll see another problem: we have 12 gutters, not 11\n\nHow do we remove a single gutter when all of our columns have a left margin of 20?\n\nThe answer is not obvious but very simple: We need a row to contain all the columns with a negative left margin of 20 px\n\nSomething neat happens here: the negative margin pulls the row to the left, and all the columns it contains with it, into a perfect alignment\n\nChildren are always affected by their parent's position, rotation, and scale, even if the children have their own properties\n\nSo how do we go from 12 single columns to various size columns?\n\n-->"]],"start1":0,"start2":0,"length1":0,"length2":25239}]],"length":25239}
